<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE - SLAVE
        VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SLAVE VALVE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303327">Figure 27.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect and mark the air lines from the slave valve by pushing on the fitting and pulling
                on the line.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mounting bolts and the washers from the slave valve. Remove the slave valve.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">On Design Level 1 Transmissions:</emph>remove and replace the gasket between the slave
                valve and the case.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">On Design Level 2 Transmissions:</emph>
                a gasket for the slave valve is not used.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the actuator pin, the spring and the sleeve from the bore in the main case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303328">Figure 28)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303327" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303327.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 27. Remove Slave Valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303328" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303328.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 28. Remove Actuator Pin, Spring, And Slave From Bore</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
